
## Date: 16/02/2026
## Module: CSS - Introduction

### Topics Covered
- Introduction to CSS
- Types of CSS (Inline, Internal, External)
- CSS Syntax and Selectors
- Applying styles to HTML elements

### Learning Summary
Today I started Module 3 which focuses on CSS fundamentals.
I learned how CSS is used to style webpages and improve the
visual appearance of HTML elements. I practiced applying
colors, fonts, and basic styling using different types of CSS.

### Practical Work
- Applied Inline CSS styling
- Created Internal CSS example
- Linked External CSS file to HTML page

### Outcome
Understood the basic structure of CSS and how styling
separates design from webpage content.
